com.i2group.apollo.events.transport

Class PropertyGroupChangeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.events.transport.PropertyGroupChangeSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IChangeSet<PropertyGroupChange,PropertyGroup>

    public final class PropertyGroupChangeSet
extends Object
implements IChangeSet<PropertyGroupChange,PropertyGroup>
    Contains information about PropertyGroups to be added to, changed in, or removed from a Card on an Item. Some commands restrict which of these lists can be populated.

    A PropertyGroupChangeSet can contain zero or more new PropertyGroups, zero or more PropertyGroupChanges, and zero or more identifiers of PropertyGroups to be removed.

    Validation:

    • After applying the PropertyGroupChangeSet, each affected PropertyGroup must contain all its mandatory Propertys.
    • The identifiers of PropertyGroups must not be empty.
    • The identifiers of PropertyGroups must not exceed the maximum permitted length of 36 bytes.
    In addition, it is invalid for a card change set that adds a card to an item to contain a property group change set that describes changed or removed property groups.

    When you amend an existing card, you are free to add, change, and remove the properties and property groups that it contains. In this situation, there are no restrictions on the contents of property group change sets that the card change set contains.

    Since:
    1.0
